definition.value: A tertiary amine having one ethyl and two 3-phenylprop-1-yl groups attached to the nitrogen. An antispasmodic that acts directly on intestinal and uterine smooth muscle, it is used (particularly as the citrate salt) in the treatment of irritable bowel syndrome.
A ketone containing a bromo substituent.
A bromoketone in which the bromine and oxo substituents are on adjacent carbon atoms.
An alpha-bromoketone that is acetone in which one of the hydrogens is replaced by a bromine atom. A poweful lachrymator, it was formerly used as a chemical weapon.
An alpha-bromoketone that is acetophenone substituted by a bromo group at position 2.
A compound containing both ketone and ester functionalities.
A ketoester where the ketone and ester functionalities are on adjacent atoms.
A ketoester where the ketone and ester functionalities are separated by a single carbon atom.
A pyruvate ester resultinf grom the formal condensation of the carboxy group of pyruvic acid with the hydroxy group of methanol.
A compound containing both ketone and nitrile functionalities.
A ketonitrile where the ketone and nitrile functionalities are on adjacent atoms.
A ketonitrile in which the cyano group and the carbonyl group are attached to the same carbon atom.
A methyl phenyl(piperidin-2-yl)acetate in which both stereocentres have S configuration. It is the inactive enantiomer in the racemic drug methylphenidate.
An epoxycarotenol that is found in brown seaweed and which exhibits anti-cancer, anti-diabetic, anti-oxidative and neuroprotective properties.
A methyl phenyl(piperidin-2-yl)acetate in which both stereocentres have R configuration.  It is the active enantiomer in the racemic drug methylphenidate.
A methyl phenyl(piperidin-2-yl)acetate that has S configuration alpha to the carbonyl group and R configuration at the stereocentre bearing the nitrogen.
A methyl phenyl(piperidin-2-yl)acetate that has R configuration alpha to the carbonyl group and S configuration at the stereocentre bearing the nitrogen.
An azoxybenzene with a trans-configuration.
A ketone of formula RC(=O)CH3 (R =/= H).
An azoxybenzene with a cis-configuration.
A diketone that has its two ketone functionalities on adjacent atoms.
A univalent group of formula BRR' (where R or R' can be H) with the free valency at the boron atom.
Compounds where two amino groups are bound to an SO2 unit.
A compound where an oxygen atom and an amino group are bound to an SO2 unit.
A member of the class of imines that is benzophenone imine carrying two dimethylamino substituents at positions 4 and 4'. The hydrochloride salt is the biological stain 'auramine O'

A hydrochloride obtained by combining 4,4'-carbonimidoylbis(N,N-dimethylaniline) with one molar equivalent of hydrogen chloride. A fluorescent stain for demonstrating acid fast organisms in a method similar to the Ziehl Neelsen. It also can be used to make a fluorescent Schiff reagent.
A compound containing two indole units.
An alkaloid containing a bisindole skeleton.
Compounds containing the asterriquinone skeleton.
A member of the class of asterriquinones that is asterriquinone in which the hydrogens of both of the hydroxy groups have replaced by methyl groups.
A member of the class of dihydroxy-1,4-benzoquinones that is asterriquinone in which the double bonds in both of the N-(3-methylbut-1-en-3-yl) groups have been reduced to single bonds.
An ester of cyanoacetic acid.
